  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Increase of Ahaz' transgressions against the Lord. - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 28:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". After this proof that Ahaz only brought greater oppression upon himself by seeking help from the king of Assyria (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 28:16-21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), there follows (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 28:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) an account of how he, in his trouble, continued to sin more and more against God the Lord, and hardened himself more and more in idolatry. לו הצר וּבעת corresponds to the ההיא בּעת ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 28:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". \"At the time when they oppressed him, he trespassed yet more against the Lord, he King Ahaz.\" In the last words the rhetorical emphasizing of the subject comes clearly out. The sentence contains a general estimation of the attitude of the godless king under the divine chastisement, which is then illustrated by facts (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 28:23-25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
